name: Vegan Pumpkin Oatmeal
description: This is a comforting way to start your morning. Made with protein-rich soy milk
info: Stir the oats, soy milk, pumpkin puree, and cinnamon together in a saucepan; bring to a gentle boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer 5 minutes, or until the oatmeal reaches your desired consistency. Transfer to serving bowl. Garnish with walnuts and honey.

name: Tuna Salad
description: A delicious and healthy tuna salad recipe
info: Chop up the tomato, cucumber, and onion. Mix together with the tuna in a bowl. Add your desired dressing and mix well. Serve on a bed of lettuce or other greens (optional). Enjoy!

name: Tuna Salad
description: A refreshing and satisfying salad made with tuna and fresh vegetables.
info: Chop up the tomato, cucumber, and onion and mix it with the tuna. Add some lettuce or other greens if you'd like. Season with salt, pepper, and lemon juice. Enjoy!

name: Fresh Tuna Salad
description: A refreshing, healthy tuna salad with diced tomato, sliced cucumber, and thinly sliced onion.
info: Mix all ingredients together with olive oil and lemon juice. Serve as a side salad or main dish.

name: Fettuccine Alfredo
description: A classic Italian pasta dish with a creamy parmesan sauce.
info:
1. Cook fettuccine in a large pot of salted boiling water until al dente. Reserve 1 cup of pasta water, then drain the pasta.
2. In a large saucepan, melt the butter over medium heat. Add the heavy cream and bring to a simmer.
3. Gradually whisk in the parmesan cheese until smooth. Season with salt and pepper.
4. Add the cooked fettuccine to the sauce and toss to coat, adding reserved pasta water as needed to loosen the sauce.
5. Serve hot with additional parmesan cheese and black pepper, if desired.

name: Tuna Salad
description: A tasty and nutritious salad made with canned tuna, fresh veggies, and your favorite dressing.
info: Simply dice up the tomato, cucumber, and onion, mix them with some canned tuna, and dress with your favorite salad dressing. Serve over greens or on toasted bread for a delicious and healthy meal.

name: Tuna Salad
description: A delicious and healthy tuna salad with fresh vegetables
info: Mix the tuna, diced tomato, cucumber, and onion together in a bowl. Serve over a bed of lettuce or spinach and top with your favorite dressing.

name: Spaghetti Carbonara
description: Traditional Italian pasta dish with creamy sauce made from eggs, parmesan cheese, and bacon or pancetta.
info:
1. Cook spaghetti in salted boiling water according to package instructions. 
2. While spaghetti is cooking, fry bacon or pancetta in a large skillet over medium heat until crispy. Add garlic and cook for another minute. 
3. In a separate bowl, whisk together eggs and parmesan cheese until smooth. 
4. Drain cooked spaghetti and immediately add to skillet with bacon and garlic. Remove skillet from heat. 
5. Pour egg mixture over spaghetti and toss quickly until spaghetti is evenly coated with sauce. 
6. Season with salt and pepper to taste. 
7. Serve hot, garnished with chopped parsley if desired.

name: Grilled Salmon with Avocado Salsa
description: Delicious and healthy grilled salmon topped with a fresh avocado salsa.
info:
1. Preheat grill to medium-high heat.
2. Brush salmon fillets with olive oil and season with salt, pepper, smoked paprika, and oregano.
3. Grill salmon for 4-5 minutes per side or until cooked to your liking.
4. In a separate bowl, combine diced avocado, red onion, jalapeno, lime juice, and cilantro to make the salsa.
5. Serve grilled salmon topped with the avocado salsa. Enjoy!

name: Mustard Roasted Chicken Thighs
description: A simple and tasty chicken dish that is perfect for a weeknight dinner or for meal prep.
info:
1. Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
2. In a small bowl, whisk together Dijon mustard, olive oil, honey, paprika, garlic powder, onion powder, salt, and black pepper.
3. Place chicken thighs on the prepared baking sheet and brush the mustard mixture on top of each thigh.
4. Roast chicken thighs in the preheated oven for 35-40 minutes, or until the internal temperature reaches 165°F (75°C).
5. Serve immediately or store in the refrigerator for up to one week.

name: Pasta Carbonara
description: A classic Italian pasta dish made with eggs, pancetta, and parmesan cheese.
info:
1. Cook spaghetti according to package instructions. 
2. While spaghetti is cooking, cook pancetta in a large skillet over medium heat until browned and crispy. 
3. In a separate bowl, whisk together eggs, parmesan cheese, salt, and pepper. 
4. Once spaghetti is cooked, drain and add to the skillet with the pancetta. 
5. Remove skillet from heat and pour egg mixture over the spaghetti. 
6. Stir until the eggs are cooked and the spaghetti is coated in the sauce. 
7. Serve hot and enjoy!

name: Creamy Garlic Shrimp Pasta
description: A delicious and easy-to-make pasta dish with sauted garlic shrimp in a creamy sauce.
ingredients: 1 lb large shrimp, peeled and deveined
info:
1. Cook pasta according to package instructions. Drain and set aside. 

2. In a large pan, heat olive oil over medium-high heat. Add garlic and saut for 1-2 minutes, until fragrant. 

3. Add shrimp to the pan and cook for 2-3 minutes on each side, until pink and cooked through. Remove shrimp from the pan and set aside. 

4. Pour white wine into the pan and let it simmer for 1-2 minutes. 

5. Add heavy cream, Parmesan cheese, salt, and black pepper to the pan. Stir well and let the sauce simmer for 2-3 minutes, until thickened. 

6. Add cooked pasta and shrimp to the pan. Toss well to combine. 

7. Serve hot and enjoy!

name: Pesto Pasta
description: A quick and easy pasta dish that's packed with flavor.
info: Cook the pasta according to the package directions. While the pasta is cooking, make the pesto. In a food processor, pulse together the basil, Parmesan cheese, olive oil, pine nuts, garlic, salt, and pepper until smooth. Drain the pasta and toss with the pesto. Serve immediately.

name: Grilled Chicken Salad
description: A healthy and delicious salad with grilled chicken
info:
1. Preheat grill to medium-high heat. 
2. Season chicken with salt and pepper and grill for about 6-8 minutes per side, or until cooked through. Let cool and then slice into strips. 
3. In a large bowl, combine mixed greens, cherry tomatoes, cucumber, avocado, and feta cheese. 
4. In a small bowl, whisk together olive oil, red wine vinegar, Dijon mustard, garlic, salt, and pepper. 
5. Drizzle dressing over salad and toss to combine. 
6. Divide salad onto plates and top with grilled chicken strips. Enjoy!

name: Creamy Garlic Chicken
description: A delicious and easy creamy garlic chicken recipe that is perfect for weeknight dinners.
info:
1. Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add minced garlic and sauté for 1-2 minutes.
2. Add chicken breasts and cook for 6-7 minutes per side or until fully cooked.
3. Remove chicken from skillet and set aside.
4. Pour chicken broth into skillet and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 3-4 minutes.
5. Add heavy cream, parmesan cheese, dried basil, salt, and black pepper. Whisk together until fully combined.
6. Add chicken back to the skillet and spoon sauce over the top. Serve immediately.
